<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   In the orphanage in Qeynos, he managed to pick up a little of the trick of putting scratches down so that others could comprehend his desires, so he takes a piece of charred wood from last night's campfire and scrawls hastily on large sheet of bark</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Qeynos Afternoon Tea</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
+5 DEX, +5 WIS, +5 INT, +5 AGI<br>
This is a miraculous drink!<br>
<br>
3 stacks for sale. Kick me if you wanna buy some, I'm tired.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   He then slumps down against the wall of a stall, huddled protectively around his pack, and nods off into the dreamless sleep of the weary.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
/ooc Please contact me in game, as I doubt I'll be checking this post before I try to auction this stuff off. If you'd like to place an order for the future, please feel free to do so here, but I cannot guarantee turnaround, as foraged supplies are not always in stock. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uchasefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChaseFV</A> at: 9/13/02 8:50:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uchasefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChaseFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/14/02 7:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=349.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Master Brewer putting out the shingle</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Chase throws his packs vehemently against the back of an empty stall near the back of the Bazaar and sits down in what can only be described as a petulant huff.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  You look at him inquiringly, your curiosity clear on your mien. He makes eye contact, frowns and begins to speak:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I trudged all the way to this horrible treeless place to offer my wares for sale, as I have recently completed some Surefall Ranger's Trail Juice (+4 DEX, +4 STA, +4 WIS), but the evil wizard Ver'Ant has cast a spell on my packs; I can't open the damned things, so I don't know how much I have left! He assures me that I'll be able to open them up in a day or so, but I still think I aughta duel that rotten, black-hearted son of an orc...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  He turns back to his packs, apparently still intending to set up shop, even though he can't offer anything. Knowing a rather attractive ranger with a birthday coming up, you inquire as to the cost. A sudden transformation overtakes Chase, and he now reminds you of that used horse dealer in East Freeport who sold your uncle that lame roan for 20K plat...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
These fine beverages can be purchased for a mere 25 plat each. They increase your mana, they increase your health and they increase your skill with your hands! No self-respecting Ranger or Paladin should be with out one. These are really quite rare, and the materials are hard to come by. I believe I have 35 left in stock, but we'll have to wait until Ver'Ant's spell wears off to find out for certain. Can I interest you in some?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  You decide that maybe your Ranger friend would be happier with a few arrows (they're a little more in-budget for a birthday), and wander on to the next stall, making a mental note to tell your friends about this interesting beverage.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
/ooc I'm temporarily out of tea, but will be stocking this weekend. I have now acquired a corking device, and am willing to attempt any stat beverages on private commission. Please post here or contact me in-game to arrange for me to meet your individual needs. I'll be trying to set up in the Bazaar when I get home. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uchasefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChaseFV</A> at: 8/14/02 9:49:15 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uchasefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChaseFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/30/02 2:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=349.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Master Brewer putting out the shingle</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  A dirty, trail-worn ranger struts into the Bazaar, reeking somewhat of fish. He pushes his way past the crowds, not stopping to look at any of the others' wares, and begins to set up shop in a little-used stall near the back of the Bazaar. His sense of purpose intrigues you, so you follow him at a distance (and upwind of him) to see what he could possibly be offering.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  He sets forth a shiny placard he has pulled from one of his packs, and you can tell by the quality of the sign and the well-written script he paid someone else to make this for him. Smirking at the inferiority of this grubby half-elf, you take a step closer to read what it says:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Fresh from the Western Sea!<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Fizzy Odus Juice</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
+4 INT, +4 DEX, +4 AGI<br>
Flowing drink!<br>
Only 10PP each!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Having recently worked up a thirst transporting people around the world, and never having seen this particular beverage before, you decide to contribute 10 platinum pieces to him, hoping to get his smelly carcass out of the Bazaar that much sooner. As you wander off sipping the beverage, you can tell it is certainly of oceanic origins, but you seem to feel a little lighter on your feet and be thinking more clearly just from keeping it in your pack. &quot;Not for entertaining, but perhaps a worthy beverage for long trips on the road,&quot; you think to yourself, making a mental note of this particular vendor for future reference.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
/ooc Got a hundred of these puppies for sale, will make it to the Bazaar as time allows. If you're interested, PST in-game or post here, and I'll make arrangements to meet you.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your  continued tolerance of my rambling,<br>
Chase <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uchasefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChaseFV</A> at: 8/30/02 2:05:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kaiwren>Kaiwren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/13/02 1:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=349.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://studentactivities.mscd.edu/ubb/avatars/avatar39.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Master Brewer putting out the shingle</span><hr size=1> I will be on Luclin this evening and would like to try one of these drinks.<br>
